{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Urgently implement all Cumberlege Report recommendations and reform the MHRA",
        "additional_details": "The 2020 First Do No Harm report exposed decades of avoidable harm from Pelvic Mesh, Sodium Valproate, and Primodos. Key recommendations remain unfulfilled.\r\nWe urge the Government to:\r\nReform the MHRA: Overhaul the regulator to ensure it is patient-centric, transparent, and prioritizes safety over industry interests.\r\nRedress Schemes: Provide financial support for victims\r\nTransparency: Enforce a mandatory register of interests for all doctors.\r\nThousands of families are still waiting for justice.",
        "background": "We call on the Government to fully implement all the recommendations of the First Do No Harm report; they must undertake a radical overhaul of the Medicines & Healthcare products Regulatory Agency (MHRA) to ensure it is more patient-focused & transparent, & provide full redress for victims of harm.",
